				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I wrote a tutorial for writing in C for the NES indeed, but using my own library. It does not have any generic things like cprintf and other standart stuff that is quite useless for real games, but does have everything you actually need to make a simple (and not so simple) games.<br /><br />Why I made my own library - it is the same reasons rainwarrior mentioned. It is easier for me to write own stuff than to figure out something not really used and documented, and I'm sure these bundled libs are not have everything that is actually needed. No music and sound effects support, for example.</div>

