					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">YeahManWAZZAP wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;if(PAD_LEFT)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;.......<br />}</div><br /><br />I thought this would theoretically do the trick, but cc65 stated that PAD_LEFT had not been defined.</div><br /><br />You can get something very close to that working, but you need to use a global variable and have your NMI take care of joypad reads for you if you don't want to explicitly read the joypad each time. If you are just learning C the NES is not the best thing to learn on. Or - if you are just learning NES, C is not the best way to learn the NES. If you want to learn 6502 assembly, then maybe you can learn the NES at the same time.</div>

